00:02:12,966 --> 00:02:14,134
First into the tank

00:02:14,134 --> 00:02:16,637
is a reinvention
of an ancient beverage.

00:02:25,646 --> 00:02:27,948
Hello, sharks.
I'm Jon fotheringham.

00:02:27,948 --> 00:02:29,082
And I'm
Dr. Eric durtschi.

00:02:29,082 --> 00:02:30,651
We're the creators
of crio,

00:02:30,651 --> 00:02:32,352
and we're seeking
$1 million

00:02:32,352 --> 00:02:35,188
in exchange for a 10%
equity stake in our business.

00:02:36,256 --> 00:02:37,724
Imagine
if you could combine

00:02:37,724 --> 00:02:39,526
two of America's
biggest passions --

00:02:39,526 --> 00:02:40,761
coffee and chocolate --

00:02:40,761 --> 00:02:44,197
into one amazing new drink
and tap into the $75 billion

00:02:44,197 --> 00:02:46,366
coffee, tea,
and chocolate markets.

00:02:46,366 --> 00:02:48,769
For thousands of years,
the Maya of central America

00:02:48,769 --> 00:02:51,271
prepared a chocolaty drink
called xocoatl --

00:02:51,271 --> 00:02:52,673
the drink of the gods.

00:02:52,673 --> 00:02:54,007
After years
of experimenting,

00:02:54,007 --> 00:02:55,876
I reinvented
this delicious drink

00:02:55,876 --> 00:02:58,145
made with
100% cocoa beans.

00:02:58,145 --> 00:02:59,446
And it's
incredibly healthy.

00:02:59,446 --> 00:03:03,350
Crio has zero fat, zero sugar,
zero cholesterol,

00:03:03,350 --> 00:03:06,053
only 10 calories per cup,
and more antioxidants

00:03:06,053 --> 00:03:07,487
than pomegranate juice
or blueberries.

00:03:07,487 --> 00:03:10,957
It also contains a natural
stimulant called theobromine

00:03:10,957 --> 00:03:13,293
that gives you long-lasting,
gentle energy.

00:03:13,293 --> 00:03:16,563
So you can say goodbye
to the spike and crash

00:03:16,563 --> 00:03:18,532
of jittery energy
you get from coffee.

00:03:18,532 --> 00:03:22,235
In short, crio is cocoa
the way it was meant to be.

00:03:22,235 --> 00:03:25,439
Now, who would like
to experience the
drink of the gods?

00:03:29,576 --> 00:03:31,645
All right, sharks,
you're really in for a treat.

00:03:31,645 --> 00:03:34,614
For $1 million,
it better be a hell of a treat.

00:03:34,614 --> 00:03:36,049
DURTSCHI: We've got
a couple of things there.

00:03:36,049 --> 00:03:38,485
Crio can be brewed at home
or in coffee shops.

00:03:38,485 --> 00:03:40,687
Now, you can
have it plain.

00:03:40,687 --> 00:03:42,489
The one that you're
going to have that's iced

00:03:42,489 --> 00:03:43,790
is called iced coconut crio.

00:03:43,790 --> 00:03:45,659
This has a little bit of cream
added to it.

00:03:51,264 --> 00:03:53,033
Oh!

00:03:53,033 --> 00:03:54,768
Ugh!

00:03:54,768 --> 00:03:55,669
Ugh.

00:03:58,238 --> 00:04:01,241
Ugh, I don't like taste
of that.

