The valuation was insane.

00:07:33,820 --> 00:07:37,157
Yeah, but, Kevin, you're basing
on the value today. They're --

00:07:37,157 --> 00:07:38,525
oh, really?
I want to pay --

00:07:38,525 --> 00:07:40,226
and I -- and I promise you,
we really wanted a deal

00:07:40,226 --> 00:07:42,329
because you guys have so much
to bring to the table.

00:07:42,329 --> 00:07:43,797
But why do you -- why did you
price it that way?
But I promise you
that next year,

00:07:43,797 --> 00:07:45,632
we will do a minimum
of $10 million in sales.

00:07:45,632 --> 00:07:47,767
I hope you do, guys.
I really, really hope you do.
We hope you prove us wrong.

00:07:47,767 --> 00:07:49,903
O'LEARY: But you guys
didn't finish the story.

00:07:49,903 --> 00:07:51,738
It's 150 years old.

00:07:51,738 --> 00:07:53,573
Mayans were drinking it.

00:07:53,573 --> 00:07:55,175
They no longer exist.

00:07:55,175 --> 00:07:56,943
[ laughter ]

00:07:56,943 --> 00:07:58,011
Thank you.
Thank you.

00:07:58,011 --> 00:07:59,579
Good luck, you two.

00:07:59,579 --> 00:08:02,315
Well, they obviously
didn't get it.

00:08:02,315 --> 00:08:04,918
Kevin, with all due respect,
you're like a broken record.

00:08:04,918 --> 00:08:06,619
I'm right every time.
It's always -- it's --

00:08:06,619 --> 00:08:08,455
you don't look at the
future. look where they
were going with it.

00:08:08,455 --> 00:08:11,358
The future is the Mayans.
