We're -- we're different
in this sense.

00:10:04,971 --> 00:10:07,707
Basically, tough mudder
is a 12-mile course, right,

00:10:07,707 --> 00:10:09,109
with about 20 obstacles.

00:10:09,109 --> 00:10:11,277
We have 25 obstacles
over three miles.

00:10:11,277 --> 00:10:14,080
So it's more about the obstacles
and less about the running.

00:10:14,080 --> 00:10:15,682
And being
a three-mile course,

00:10:15,682 --> 00:10:17,050
it's much more accessible
to the general public

00:10:17,050 --> 00:10:19,085
than something like
a 12-mile course would be.

00:10:19,085 --> 00:10:21,087
Are you saying this
is a tamer version of that --

00:10:21,087 --> 00:10:22,889
something that Barbara
would do?

00:10:22,889 --> 00:10:24,457
Oh, I could handle
the 12 miles.

00:10:24,457 --> 00:10:26,359
It's this little short guy
over here

00:10:26,359 --> 00:10:27,894
that wouldn't have a shot
at it.

00:10:27,894 --> 00:10:30,730
Uh, but we get people
of all shapes and sizes
at our events, truly,

00:10:30,730 --> 00:10:32,532
from 77-year-old guys to,
you know,

00:10:32,532 --> 00:10:35,034
mother/daughter teams,
14-year-old and up.

00:10:35,034 --> 00:10:36,970
Is it more workout
or more party?

00:10:36,970 --> 00:10:38,771
We think we strike
an excellent balance

00:10:38,771 --> 00:10:40,406
between the workout
and the party.

00:10:40,406 --> 00:10:41,774
Because it's a shorter race,
it takes, you know,

00:10:41,774 --> 00:10:43,977
an average of an hour
or a little bit more to finish.

00:10:43,977 --> 00:10:46,679
People are -- are exhausted,
but they're still exhilarated.

